In this repo I include some customized scripts and
applications to plurk. 
#Apps:
---------------------------------------------------------
### command-line-plurker (aka plurkEs.pl) ###
#Description:
This is a Perl program
translated to Spanish. It is a  
customization of pkrumins (http://www.plurk.com/pkrumins)
program called "command-line-plurker".
#Installation
0. Requirements
Perl modules required: WWW::Mechanize, LWP::UserAgent
Before you  should check if these modules are installed:
instmod (as root)
if these modules are not installed:
perl -MCPAN -e shell (as root)
inside CPAN shell type: install module
#Usage
1. Just type ./plurkEs ? to see available options
Basic usage: 
plurkEs.pl -a shares http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QcPvHkXfqoc \(Algo de The Clash para empezar\)
In case you don not use a modifier action 'says' is default used:
plurkEs.pl Ya estoy \(hungry\)
Happy console plurking!!!
